<DOC><DOCNO> AP880916-0236 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-16-88 0257EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-BusinessHighlights 2Takes   09-16 0548</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Business Highlights, 2 Takes,0574</SECOND><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Retail sales declined in August for only thesecond time this year, the government has reported, indicating toanalysts that inflationary pressures are easing.   The Commerce Department said Thursday that sales fell by 0.2percent last month to $133.5 billion.   Economists have been worried since the spring that rising exportsales coupled with strong demand from U.S. consumers would put toomuch strain on the economy and fuel inflation.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The U.S. industrial operating rate rose forthe fifth consecutive month in August, the Federal Reserve Boardsays.   Economists played down the inflationary effect of the increaseannounced Thursday because it stemmed entirely from a temporarysummer surge at utilities.   The Fed said the nation's factories, mines and utilitiesoperated at 83.7 percent of capacity last month, a 0.1 percentagepoint increase over July.</TEXT><DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Management officials at Hospital Corp.of America are trying to line up financing for a $3.3 billionbuyout of the company, one of the world's biggest hospital chains.   The company said Thursday that a group of managers had advisedthe board of directors about its intended proposal of $47 a sharein cash for HCA's 70.6 million shares outstanding.   HCA said Chairman Thomas F. Frist Jr. plans to negotiate withunidentified third parties to obtain financing for the proposal,known as a leveraged buyout.</TEXT><DATELINE>ROCKY HILL, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ames Department Stores Inc. said it hasagreed to buy Zayre Corp.'s 388-unit discount store division in adeal it valued at about $800 million.   Peter Hollis, Ames' president and chief executive officer, saidThursday that the deal would double the number of discount storesthat Ames operates, and lift Ames to third place from fifth amongthe nation's largest discount retailers.   Ames operates 348 discount stores, primarily in small towns in18 states in the Northeast and mid-Atlantic regions. Zayre discountstores are in 26 states and the District of Columbia.</TEXT><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   British publisher Robert Maxwell has raised hisoffer for Macmillan Inc. to $2.41 billion in cash, a surprise moveto counter a $2.36 billion deal for the U.S. publishing giant madeby the investment firm Kohlberg Kravis Roberts andamp; Co. earlier thisweek.   Maxwell, who previously offered $84 for each of the company's27.76 million shares, said Thursday he now was willing to pay$86.80. He also offered to pay the company's recently declared20-cent quarterly dividend.   As an alternative, Maxwell said, his Sept. 8 offer to purchase11 Macmillan information businesses for $1.4 billion still was good.</TEXT><DATELINE>GREENWICH, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Brands Inc. says it hasreceived and rebuffed a buyout proposal from an investor group ledby financier Bennett LeBow, who alternatively requested a chance tobuy the company's tobacco businesses.   American Brands said late Thursday the group had filed forfederal antitrust clearance to acquire more than $15 million worthof the company's stock, and might acquire more than 50 percent ofAmerican Brands' outstanding shares.   LeBow indicated he wanted to discuss a negotiated, cash buyoutof American Brands at a ``significant premium'' to the market price.   American Brands closed at $48.37{ a share Thursday, down 37{cents in New York Stock Exchange trading.</TEXT><NOTE>MORE</NOTE></DOC>